'''The West Cork Chamber Music Festival''' is a music festival, established in 1995,<ref>{{Cite web|title = West Cork Music 2016 About|url = http://www.westcorkmusic.ie/about|website = www.westcorkmusic.ie|access-date = 2016-01-14}}</ref> that takes place in the town of [[Bantry]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]], usually in July.
==Performers== Performers at the festival have included the [[RTÉ Vanbrugh Quartet]], [[Barry Douglas (musician)|Barry Douglas]], [[Ruby Hughes]], [[Nicola Benedetti]], [[Tanja Becker-Bender]] and [[Natalie Clein]] <ref>{{Cite web|title = WCM Archive - Homepage|url = http://archive.westcorkmusic.ie|website = archive.westcorkmusic.ie|access-date = 2016-01-14}}</ref> and works have included some by contemporary composers, such as [[Thomas Larcher]] and [[Mathias Hinke]].
== Venues and activities == [[File:Bantry House.jpg|thumb|Bantry House has been a central venue for the West Cork Chamber Music Festival]] The performances take place at venues around the town, including [[Bantry House]] and St Brendan's Church. The central performance venue is Bantry House, where the drawing room, with a capacity of approximately 50 seats, is used for some concerts.
Alongside the performances the festival includes violin and bow making, master classes and a composition competition whose past winners include [[Harry Whalley]], Sebastian Adams and Solfa Carlisle.
== Composition competition == The festival runs a composition competition <ref>http://www.westcorkmusic.ie/chambermusicfestival/uploads/pdf/WCCMF_Composition_Competition_2008_to_2015.pdf</ref> for young composers born or resident of Ireland under the age of 35.
